text=!!Making requests for what you want%0a[[#excerpt]]%0aIn order to get the things you want, often you have to request things of someone. This can also be used for self-directed actions, i.e., you are making requests of yourself.%0a[[#excerptend]]%0a%0a'''Presupposition:''' both parties are willing to negotiate to a consensus.%0a%0a'''Presupposition:''' the intention of both parties is to produce (realize) the outcome.%0a%0a'''Presupposition:''' all behavior is the result of an initial good intention from the point of view of actor.%0a%0aAn '''outcome''' is often divided into two parts: a '''request''' and a '''commitment''' are two halves of a whole '''Conversation For Action''' (a concept put forth by Terry Winograd of Stanford University). The purpose of the conversation is to have a person make a request of another person, the second person commit (or promise) to fulfill the request.%0a%0a* a '''request''' is in the form of a question%0a* a '''commitment''' is in the form of an assertion%0a%0a!!Canonical Request Form:%0a%0a-> "I request that you perform ''X'' delivering ''Y'' by time ''T''"%0a%0a!!Canonical Response Forms:%0a%0aOne of:%0a%0a# "I accept."%0a# "I decline."%0a# A counteroffer to negotiate the specifications of ''X'', ''Y'', and ''T''. "I can't do ''X'' but I can do ''X&#39;'', by date ''T&#39;''. Is that ok?"%0a# A commitment to a future commitment ("I can't tell you now, but I'll get back to you about it on ''date''."%0a%0aAll requests require a response; there is no such thing as silence equals agreement. The opposite is the case: if no response is made, the requestor should consider the request declined.%0a%0aThe [[well-formedness of the outcome / request / commitment -> WellFormedOutcomes]] is the result of the full and independent commitment of both parties agreeing to and having, or being able to aquire, the resources, skills and knowledge to achieve the outcome / request / commitment. Each party is completely and independently responsible for the [[well-formedness -> WellFormedOutcomes]] of the outcome / request / commitment.%0a%0a>>comment%3c%3c%0aThis goes at the bottom of the page, hidden by comment block class%0aSummary:Getting the results you want%0aParent:Consulting(.HomePage)%0aIncludeMe:[[{Consulting.HomePage]]%0aCategories:[[!Articles]]%0aTags: well-formed, requests, commitment%0a(:tags-hide well-formed, requests, commitment:)%0a>>%3c%3c%0a
